added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: The Metric System vs. Freedom
added.description: Robin teaches the other Titans about the difference between the Imperial System and the Metric System.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: The Fair
added.description: The Baby Bears make a deal with a carnival worker to be prizes for a game of ball toss.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Teacher's Pet
added.description: The Baby Bears escape their hectic lives by attending school.

added.title: The Line
added.description: The family has waited in line outside the movie theater all night. They are devastated when Larry tells them they won't get into the first screening of the Stellar Odyssey sequel. But, hardcore fans that they are, the Wattersons are determined to be the first to see the movie and so set about battling their way to the front of the queue.

added.title: The Law
added.description: Donut Cop shows Gumball and Darwin that the smallest misdemeanour can lead to a breakdown in law.  Gumball jaywalks and is pulled over by Donut Cop. When Gumball objects he is told that even the smallest misdemeanor can lead to a breakdown in law. In an effort to impress the kids Donut Cop takes them for a ride-along in his cop car and gets carried away, progressively breaking the law himself. He soon proves that the tiniest offense can indeed snowball into complete lawlessness!

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Limit
added.description: The Watterson family faces Mom's wrath in a supermarket.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: Roundabout Part 1
added.description: Forever Knight finally assembles his Round Table of young but super-powerful Knights, including— Ben?! With Ben's help, Forever Knight leads his new minions in an all-out attack on a Particle Accelerator - his true intention to transform it into a Time Machine and conquer history!

added.title: Forever Road
added.description: During a drag race, Ben hopes to stay neck and neck with Vin Ethanol and La Grange as XLR8, but when his watch keeps shorting out, our hero must get creative if he is to keep up with his fast and furious foes!

added.title: Prey or Play
added.description: After receiving a super-exclusive ticket to Adrenaland, Ben leaves behind Grandpa Max and Gwen to enjoy the perks of being the parks only attendant, but when he learns he's not alone, our hero must now contend with the only kid who could afford the price of admission: Billy Billions!

added.title: The Night Ben Tennyson Came to Town
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to Wheeler, "the liveliest mining town on Route 66", but when Ben becomes paranoid that the Forever Knight is out to get him, he must try to convince his fam while also stopping his new foe from destroying the town.

added.title: Fear in the Family
added.description: Ben and Gwen can't wait for the Omni-Copter to arrive at the Great Pyramids, but when bad weather disrupts their flight, they soon come face-to-face with The Fogg and its spawn: The Fogg Family!

added.title: Winter Creeklympics
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP try their luck at winning Gold in their first ever, Winter Creeklympics!

added.title: Welcome to Creek Street
added.description: Craig and his friends create their own neighborhood in the snow!

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Hic Hic Hooray
added.description: Bridgette gets the hiccups and becomes desperate to get rid of them.

added.title: Bananas & Cheese
added.description: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

added.title: Inglorious Toddlers
added.description: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Apple and Onion must conquer their obsessions of sausages and a video game.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion have to prove that they're not selfish when they do their good deeds.

added.title: The Music Store Thief
added.description: Apple and Onion have to defend the music store from instrument theft to get a key to the store.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion get lost beneath their floorboards and must find a way out.

added.title: It's the Little Things
added.description: When Tom drinks a potion given to him by a Gypsy woman and shrinks to the size of an insect, he must beg Jerry Van Mouseling for help in finding a cure.

added.title: Always Say Never Again
added.description: Tom and Jerry are hired by a British super spy to help guard the Queen's precious objects while they are on display in the city.

added.title: Into the Woods
added.description: When an accident leaves Jerry wrapped head to toe in bandages and unable to take his scout troop camping, a guilt-ridden Tom decides to lead the kids into the woods himself.

added.title: Ball of Fire
added.description: The hot dog relish that Crooked Eddie brings to the detectives turns out to be an explosive device that Tom and Jerry must now return to the lab before it inadvertently blows up the entire city.

added.title: Mice Fair Ladies
added.description: Jerry's cousins pay a return visit to the Manor eager to create mayhem for Tom, things get crazier than ever when the cousins wives show up as well.

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Booby-Traps, and How To Survive Them
added.description: The ninja team up with a reluctant Clutch Powers to enter a mysterious pyramid where they inadvertently unleash an ancient evil.

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: #TheBirdAndTheBee
added.description: Meek little Karen Beecher is intimidated by big broody Carter Hall - both as a hero and a teen - until she discovers Hawkman's tragically romantic destiny and vows to use her vast knowledge of cheesy teen movies to help him reunite with his beloved.

added.title: #SchoolGhoul
added.description: When Tatsu Yamashiro asks for help at a haunted all-girls academy, Barbara Gordon and Kara Danvers find themselves caught up in something much bigger than a ghost hunt.

added.title: King of the Machines
added.description: Panthro gets insecure when he finds out Barbastella has a history of dating royalty, so he tries to impress her by becoming "King of the Machines" and giving all the appliances in the Cats' Lair artificial intelligence.

added.title: Sword Heist
added.description: When a local sword shop sells an ultra powerful sword to Ratar-O, Lion-O decides he has to steal it before Ratar-O can come pick it up. Unfortunately Lion-O is completely against stealing, but luckily he knows someone who loves to steal, Lion-S!

added.title: Claudus
added.description: Lion-O's dad King Claudus arrives on Third Earth, and turns out to be a big selfish jerk! Now Lion-O has to deal with his dad before he goes to war with the rest of the Thundercats.

added.title: Telethon
added.description: In order to save the Berbils, Cheetara uses her psychic powers to project a telethon into the brains of everyone on Third Earth.

added.title: Mall-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra builds a mall that's actually a giant labyrinth designed to trap the Thundercats forever. Too bad the Thundercats love the mall so much they could literally spend all eternity there.

added.title: Onion Trade
added.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: Marble Madness
added.description: Steven and the Gems encounter another droid from space.

added.title: Political Power
added.description: The Gems cause a power outage in Beach City, and Steven helps Mayor Dewey do damage control.

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.

added.title: I Am a Sword
added.description: Finn starts having guilt nightmares about his missing Finn Sword but are the nightmares real?

added.title: Is That You?
added.description: After a memorial for a fallen ally, Jake starts acting very strange.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Ignition Point
added.description: When Finn and Jake sneak into the Fire Kingdom, they get caught in the middle of a Flame family feud.

added.title: I Remember You
added.description: Ice King and Marceline share a tender and revealing few moments reminiscing.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: In an effort to prove to Master Frown that she is no tyrant, Unikitty agrees to hold an election to see who will be the new princess of the Unikingdom. In a shock, Master Frown takes an early lead in the poles. Unikitty discovers Frown is winning because he's cheating. Will she resort to her own dirty tricks to win the election or stay true to her self and try to win by being nice?

added.title: Delivery Effect
added.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

added.title: First Flight
added.description: The gang is taking an airplane trip together, and Hawk is at the helm since today he's taking his captain's license test. However Richard is terrified of flying, so Unikitty & Puppycorn spend the chaotic flight trying to help Rick conquer his fear of flying while Dr Fox joins Hawk in the cockpit to help him pass his test. After a destructive and dangerous flight, Rick makes it safetly back on the ground (after surviving the plane crashing). Hawk fails his test but gets to take it again next week, so the gang is excited for another free flight.

added.title: Cheerleading
added.description: Brock drags Master Frown along to join him in following his dream, to become the Flyer on a cheerleading team. They team up with Unikitty & the gang and go head to head against Really Old Edith and her rival cheer team of meanies. But when the gang finds Brock is too heavy to be the Flyer they're forced to try a bunch of ridiculous ways to get him off the ground.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Super Amazing Raft Adventure
added.description: Unikitty and Hawkodile are "lost at sea", stranded on a raft together. Hawkodile sees this as an opportunity to show Unikitty that he's prepared for anything with his expertly-honed survival skills, but to his shock, all of his plans keep falling apart, while Unikitty's silly "it'll all work out, let's have fun" approach is somehow working great! Will Hawkodile manage to let go of his overpreparedness to save them both, or will Unikitty whimsical fun be their doom?

added.title: Tragic Magic
added.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Two Lies, One Truth
added.description: As Lloyd unmasks Mystake for who she truly is, Emperor Garmadon embraces Harumi as his daughter of darkness. Meanwhile, Wu holds onto faith as he leads his friends into dangerous Oni territory in the hope of finding Firstbourne's nest

added.title: Dos mentiras una verdad
added.description: Cuando Lloyd desenmascara y revela la identidad de Mystake, el Emperador Garmadon acepta a Harumi como su hija de la oscuridad. Mientras tanto, Wu se aferra a su fe al llevar a sus amigos hacia territorios Oni peligrosos esperando encontrar el nido de la Primogénita.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El eslabon mas debil
added.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Weakest Link
added.description: Lloyd turns the tables on Harumi to take his father's power away, and the Ninja learn what it takes to be a Dragon Hunter.

added.title: Saving Faith
added.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

added.title: Salvando a Faith
added.description: Lloyd y su equipo planean tomar el control del Oni Titan. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, los Ninja caen en las garras del Barón de Hierro y un viejo maestro regresa.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Lessons for a Master
added.description: When Iron Baron forces Wu to retrieve the Dragon Armor, things don't go as planned. In Ninjago, Lloyd can only endure so much as he holds onto hope for the Ninjas' return.

added.title: Lecciones para un maestro
added.description: Cuando el Barón de Hierro obliga a Wu a tomar la Armadura de Dragón, las cosas no salen como se planearon. En Ninjago, hay un límite de lo que Lloyd puede soportar mientras se aferra a la esperanza del regreso de los Ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Destino verde
added.description: Los Ninjas regresan por fin a casa y se unen para detener al Emperador Garmadon, obligando a Lloyd a tomar una decisión que cambiará por siempre a Ninjago.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Green Destiny
added.description: The Ninja finally return home and unite to stop Emperor Garmadon, forcing Lloyd to make a decision that will forever change Ninjago.

added.title: Maellard's Package
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to wait at Maellard's mansion and get a very important delivery.

added.title: Marvolo the Wizard
added.description: Pops thinks that he's a wizard trapped in medieval times, and he wants to go back home.

added.title: The End of Muscle Man
added.description: The guys want to help Muscle Man finish his bucket list.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: Party Horse
added.description: The guys want to help Party Horse pass his U.S. history test.

added.title: La Parisina
added.description: Cuando Starfire se obsesiona con una cuchara para servir helado, los demás intentan enseñarle que los objetos inanimados no pueden reemplazar a las personas.

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: El sistema metrico versus la libertad
added.description: Robin le enseña a los demás Titanes acerca de las diferencias entre el sistema imperial y el sistema métrico.

added.title: El demonio
added.description: Por accidente, Chloe y Polar pierden la chaqueta con capucha que tanto quiere Chloe en las garras del feroz perro de la tienda de al lado. Se embarcan en una misión para recuperarla.

added.title: La feria
added.description: Los Osos bebés hacen un trato con un empleado del parque de atracciones para convertirse en premios de un juego de lanzamiento de pelota.

added.title: El viaje
added.description: Chloe y los osos hacen un viaje en auto para ver una lluvia de meteoritos. Polar, el único que tiene licencia de conducir, está a cargo del manejo, lo cual se vuelve más difícil de lo que pensaba.

added.title: Dia de Spa
added.description: Los Osos se relajan en el spa. Grizz intenta usar todos los servicios del spa. Panda queda atrapado en la sala de vapor con un anciano. Y Polar juega al ping pong.

added.title: El Favorito de la Profesora
added.description: Los ositos van a la escuela para escapar de sus vidas agitadas.

added.title: Rodeo Parte 1
added.description: El Caballero por Siempre finalmente reúne a su Mesa Redonda de Caballeros jóvenes pero superpoderosos... i¿incluido Ben?! Con la ayuda de Ben, el Caballero lidera a sus nuevos súbditos en un ataque generalizado contra un acelerador de partículas.

added.title: Miedo en la Familia
added.description: Ben y Gwen están ansiosos por que el Omni-Copter llegue a las Grandes Pirámides. Pero cuando el mal tiempo interrumpe su vuelo, pronto se enfrentan cara a cara con Neblina y sus engendros: iLa familia Niebla!

added.title: Carretera por Siempre
added.description: Durante una carrera de aceleración, Ben espera mantenerse al mismo nivel con Vin Etanol y La Grange como XLR8. Pero cuando su reloj hace cortocircuito una y otra vez, nuestro héroe debe ser creativo si quiere seguir el ritmo de sus rápidos y furiosos enemigos.

added.title: Caza o Juego
added.description: Después de recibir un billete superexclusivo para Adrenalandia, Ben deja atrás al abuelo Max y a Gwen para disfrutar de las ventajas de ser el único asistente del parque. Pero pronto se entera de que no está solo.

added.title: La noche que Ben Tennyson vino al pueblo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson viaja a Wheeler, "la ciudad minera más animada de la Ruta 66". Pero cuando Ben se pone paranoico con la idea de que el Caballero por Siempre lo esté persiguiendo, debe tratar de convencer a su familia al mismo tiempo que evita que su nuevo enemigo destruya la ciudad.

added.title: Lord Vaquero Darrell
added.description: Todos se ven obligados a enfrentar grandes cambios en Boxmore.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Lord Cowboy Darrell
added.description: Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.

added.title: Body Trouble
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Belly Bag have a disagreement, they separate and try to make each other jealous.

added.title: Festival de Cine en la Plaza
added.description: Cuando se organiza un festival de cine propio en la Plaza, iEnid y Rad están seguros de que su obra ganará!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Plaza Film Festival
added.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Dia de elecciones
added.description: En un esfuerzo por demostrarle a Master Frown que no es una tirana, Unikitty acuerda celebrar una elección para ver quién será la nueva princesa del Unireino. En una situación sorpresiva, Master Frown toma una ventaja temprana en las encuestas. Unikitty descubre que Frown gana porque está haciendo trampa. ¿Recurrirá Unikitty a sus propios trucos sucios para ganar las elecciones o permanecerá fiel a sí misma y seguirá tratando de ganar gracias a su amabilidad?

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: Efecto Entrega
added.description: Unikitty y su banda pidieron una deliciosa comida tailandesa para la cena. Por desgracia, la espera para la entrega se está haciendo demasiado larga y hasta el tiempo parece pasar más lento. En un esfuerzo por conseguir la comida más rápido, la banda utiliza la máquina del tiempo de la Dra. Fox, lo cual causa graves problemas y hiere profundamente los sentimientos del Padre Tiempo.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: Primer Vuelo
added.description: Cuando la banda hace un viaje en avión, Halcondrilo está al mando ya que hoy da el examen para obtener su licencia de capitán. Como a Richard le da terror volar, Unikitty y Perricornio pasan el caótico vuelo tratando de ayudarlo a vencer su miedo, mientras la Dra. Fox acompaña a Halcondrilo en la cabina para ayudarlo a aprobar su examen.

added.title: Los Porristas
added.description: Brock convence a Master Frown de acompañarlo para hacer realidad su sueño de convertirse en el volador de un equipo de animadoras. Se asocian con Unikitty y la banda y se enfrentan cara a cara con Edith y el equipo de porristas malvados que tienen como rivales. Pero cuando la banda descubre que Brock es demasiado pesado para ser el volador, se ven obligados a intentar un montón de formas ridículas de levantarlo del suelo.

added.title: Pijamada Misteriosa
added.description: KO, Enid y Rad intentan resolver un misterio.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Fiesta de Monstruos
added.description: Enid debe tomar una decisión cuando llegan sus antiguos amigos de la Escuela de monstruos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: El Vientre del Monstruo
added.description: Para reparar el Land-Bounty, el ninja debe recuperar un componente crítico del motor que ha sido tragado por un escarabajo gigante.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Trampas y Como Sobrevivir a Ellas
added.description: El ninja se une a un clutch Powers renuente para entrar en una misteriosa pirámide donde desatan sin darse cuenta un antiguo mal.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Heroes Locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Ene-Amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: El Miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Enredos Perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Bajo los Reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: Rise and Shine
added.description: A glimpse at the wild, secret adventures Clarence undertakes each day before the rest of us, and the sun, get up.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Brain Game
added.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Hip hip Hurra
added.description: Bridgette tiene hipo y está desesperada por librarse de ellos.

added.title: Bananas y Queso
added.description: Duncan está decidido a evitar que el dúo Banana y Queso se presente en la guardería.

added.title: Ninos vergonzosos
added.description: Owen teme perder a su mejor amigo Noah que se va a una escuela militar.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Out of My Head
added.description: Axel must help Sarge and Bobbie learn to walk in each other's shoes - literally - after Luka unwittingly switches the toys' heads!

added.title: Freeze!
added.description: Axel and his team find themselves in a tough position after Ice Crusher makes it too cold for them to fight back at full speed.

added.title: Big Bad Dreams
added.description: When Namagem starts using his Hypno powers to haunt Aki's dreams, our hero must face his fears in the dreamscape.

added.title: License to Drill
added.description: Mega Man teams up with Bert Wily to take down Drill Man, whose plan to construct hundreds of drill shaped high rises has put Silicon City in both aesthetic and physical danger!

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Big Trouble for Tiny Miracle
added.description: Tiny Miracle allows the gang to take advantage of his generosity at the expense of his own health.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
added.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

added.title: From Hedorium to Eternity
added.description: 11-year-old Ben, Gwen, and friends go on the adventure of a lifetime in their own backyard.

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: Ego - Egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

added.title: Salchichas y Dulce Golpe
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben superar sus obsesiones por las salchichas y los videojuegos.

added.title: Fuera de Mi Cabeza
added.description: iAxel debe ayudar a Sarge y Bobbie a aprender a caminar en los zapatos del otro, literalmente, después de que Luka involuntariamente cambia las cabezas de los juguetes!

added.title: La Explosion de Fuego Colosal
added.description: Cuando Colosal sale de un extraño estado de creatividad producto de una concentración extrema, es posible que haya hecho algo que podría destruir el Valle Puro Corazón entero.

added.title: El Ladron de Musica
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín tienen que defender la tienda de música del robo de instrumentos para conseguir una llave de la tienda.

added.title: Burlate con Todas tus Fuerzas
added.description: Cuando Adorabat empieza a interrumpir agresivamente a todos con su nuevo poder que le da energía, se convierte en una amenaza para el reino entero.

added.title: Entremedias
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín se pierden debajo de las tablas de madera del suelo y deben encontrar la salida.

added.title: La Mosca
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben deshacerse de una mosca que se metió en su apartamento o enfrentarse al desalojo.

added.title: Congelados
added.description: Axel y su equipo se encuentran en una posición difícil después de que Ice Crusher hace demasiado frío para que puedan defenderse a toda velocidad.

added.title: Principito perricornio
added.description: Puppycorn por fin se da cuenta de que es un príncipe, iy quiere estar a cargo del reino por una vez! A pesar de las preocupaciones de sus amigos, Unikitty permite que Puppycorn sea el rey, pero pronto, el poder absoluto en las manos del cachorro se le hace difícil de manejar, y sus ideas no son lo que se diría muy geniales. ¿Podrán removerlo del poder mientras evitan un levantamiento del pueblo?

added.title: Licencia para Golpear
added.description: A Hawkodile lo atrapa la policía de acción por trabajar como guardaespaldas sin licencia de acción. No puede proteger el reino ni hacer nada radical hasta tener la licencia, ipero la prueba en el Departamento de Caos y Violencia es para los nerds! Obligado a quitarse los guantes, Hawkodile lucha por vivir una vida sin golpes, por lo que Unikitty promete ayudar a su amigo a contener su impulso de entrar en acción y a estudiar para la prueba. Pero la prueba consiste en algo más de lo que parece.

added.title: La Super Increible Aventura en Balsa
added.description: Unikitty y Hawkodile están "perdidos en el mar," varados en una balsa juntos. Hawkodile ve esto como una oportunidad para mostrarle a Unikitty que está preparado para cualquier cosa con sus habilidades de experto en supervivencia, pero para su sorpresa, todos sus planes fracasan, mientras que la tonta postura de Unikitty de "todo saldrá bien, vamos a divertirnos" está funcionando de una manera genial. ¿Será Hawkodile capaz de soltar su exceso de preparación para salvarlos a ambos, o acaso la diversión caprichosa de Unikitty será su perdición?

added.title: Magia Tragica
added.description: Cuando Richard monta un espectáculo de magia amateur, la Dra. Fox se obsesiona por descubrir cómo se hacen esos trucos que desafían la ciencia. Pero mientras se propone usar todo su intelecto para encontrar formas experimentales de hacer los trucos que vio en la fiesta del cachorro, ¿acaso arruinará accidentalmente el asombro de la magia?

added.title: Senor Casero
added.description: El propietario amenazó a Master Frown y a Brock con desalojarlos a menos que arreglen el daño que le hicieron a su apartamento. Preocupado, Brock invita a Unikitty y a la pandilla para que los ayuden. En lugar de hacer lo que los chicos quieren en su casa, Unikitty procede a hacer lo que ella quiere. Al darse cuenta de su error, devuelve el apartamento a su antiguo estado asqueroso, pero ahora Frown y Brock están en peligro de desalojo de nuevo. Deben aliarse a Unikitty y la banda para luchar contra el malvado casero y salvar su hogar.
